<p>l. 1, there was perhaps a reference to the <foreign lang="grc">εἰσωσται</foreign> (<foreign lang="grc">ἰσωσται</foreign>) but one would have expected the article before it; the opening of the owner's name in the genitive case ended the line, and the beginning of l. 2 suggests that he was a Roman citizen and, given the likely date, with the nomen Aurelius (though this cannot be certain).</p>
</div><div type="translation">
